The article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House regarding the continuation of the national emergency with respect to Sudan. The letter explains that the crisis caused by the actions and policies of the Sudanese government, which led to the declaration of a national emergency in 1997, has not been resolved. These actions and policies are seen as a threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, President Obama has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency and maintain sanctions against Sudan.